<html>
<head>

<style type="text/css">

body {
  display: block;
  padding: 10px 15px;
  font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-size: 11px;
  min-height: 40em;
  }
h2 { font-size: 18px; }
h3 { font-size: 16px; }
h4 { font-size: 14px; }
h2, h3, h4 { margin-bottom: .2em; }

p { margin-bottom: .5em; }

a { text-decoration: underline; }
a:hover { text-decoration: none; }

</style>

</head>

<body>

<div id="c3-instructions">

<h2>Guidelines for creating a non-partisan voter guide</h2>

<p>For non-partisan voter guides, you can endorse legislation that is coming before the voters (i.e. ballot measures, initiatives, propositions), but <strong>you cannot endorse candidates.</strong></p>

<p>To include candidates in your voter guide, you should send the candidates a questionnaire asking for their positions on 5-6 issues.<br />
If you are endorsing ballot measures in your voter guide, do not ask for the candidates' positions on these measures (since this would imply your preference). </p>

<h4>Requirements for Candidate Questionnaires:</h4>
<ul>
<li>Must be sent to all candidates</li>
<li>Responses must be published verbatim <em>(a good reason to ask yes/no questions, which we highly recommend)</em></li>
<li>Questions must be framed without bias. <ul>
    <li>NOT OK: <em>"The Iraq war is killing thousands unnecessarily.  When do you think we should pull out?"</em></li>
    <li>OK: <em>"Do you support pulling our troops out of Iraq by the end of the year?"</em></li></ul>
<li>Organizations may not coordinate or cooperate with the candidates <em>(i.e. you cant help candidates fill out the questionnaire)</em></li>
</ul>

<p>If candidates do not return your questionnaire...<br />
You may print that they did not answer your questionnaire, but you still may not print information on their positions from any other source.</p>
</div>

<% if @recently_created_guide -%>
<%= link_to 'continue', :action => 'new' %>
<% elsif @recently_updated_guide_legal_status -%>
<%= link_to 'continue', :action => 'edit', :id => @guide %>
<% else -%>
<%= link_to_function 'Close this window', 'window.close()' %>
<% end -%>

</body>
</html>
